# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

## Summary
Successfully implemented Vercel Web Analytics for the WealthForge frontend application following the official Vercel documentation for React/Vite projects.

## Changes Made

### Modified Files:
- **src/App.jsx** - Added the `<Analytics />` component to enable web analytics tracking

## Implementation Details

The `@vercel/analytics` package (v1.5.0) was already installed in the project dependencies. The implementation involved:

1. **Analytics Component Integration**: Added the `<Analytics />` component from `@vercel/analytics/react` to the main App component. The import statement was already present, but the component was not being rendered.

2. **Placement**: The Analytics component was placed at the end of the main fragment in App.jsx, after the Routes component. This ensures that analytics tracking is initialized for all routes in the application.

3. **Framework Compatibility**: This implementation follows the official Vercel Web Analytics documentation for React applications using Vite as the build tool.

## How It Works

The Analytics component:
- Automatically tracks page views across all routes
- Integrates seamlessly with React Router DOM (already in use in the project)
- Will send tracking data to `/_vercel/insights/view` endpoint when deployed to Vercel
- Works in both development and production environments

## Next Steps for Deployment

To fully activate Web Analytics:
1. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard for this project (Analytics tab → Enable)
2. Deploy the application to Vercel using `vercel deploy` or via Git integration
3. Once deployed, visit the Analytics tab in the Vercel dashboard to view visitor data and page views

## Testing

- ✅ Build completed successfully (`npm run build`)
- ✅ No new linting errors introduced
- ✅ Component properly imported and rendered in the JSX tree
- ✅ Analytics will activate automatically when deployed to Vercel

## Technical Notes

- The project uses React 19.1.1 and React Router DOM 7.9.4
- Build tool: Vite 7.1.9
- Analytics package: @vercel/analytics@1.5.0
- No additional configuration or dependencies required
- The Analytics component is lightweight and doesn't impact performance
